# Testing inverted character classes. There's a curious symmetry here:
# we could just as well write "Consonant ← &[^aeiou] [a-z]". This seems
# a little odd.

Word :: char * ← Consonant Vowel Consonant { ref_str() }
Vowel ← [aeiou]
Consonant ← &[a-z] [^aeiou]
